# Database & data model

## Use (current architecture — matches this codebase)
- `inventory_catalog_items` — master item rows per list
- `inventory_lists` — list containers
- `par_guides`, `par_guide_items` — PAR definitions and levels
- `inventory_sessions`, `inventory_session_items` — count sessions and lines
- `smart_order_runs`, `smart_order_run_items` — suggested orders from counts
- `purchase_orders`, `purchase_order_items` — formal POs (after submit)
- `invoices`, `invoice_items`, `stock_movements` — receiving workflow

## Legacy — do not build new features on
- `inventory_items`, `par_items` — old model; prefer catalog + par guides
- `categories` tied to old items — avoid for new work

## PAR source of truth
PAR for ordering/risk should come from **`par_guide_items.par_level`** for the relevant guide (and list linkage), not from ad-hoc defaults. Syncing **`inventory_catalog_items.default_par_level`** from a guide is OK when explicitly implemented as sync — do not treat catalog default as the canonical PAR for analytics without that contract.

## Confusing names
- **`orders` / `order_items`** — kitchen-style orders in schema, **not** purchase orders. Purchase flow uses **`purchase_orders`** / **`smart_order_runs`**.
- **`import_runs`** vs **`inventory_import_files`** — overlapping import tracking; prefer the path the app already uses for new code.

## Migrations
Schema changes only via **`supabase/migrations/`** SQL files, not ad-hoc dashboard edits without a matching migration.
